/*

Java me String ek class hai (primitive nahi).

Key points:

String = sequence of characters

Internally stored as char[] (Java 8 tak) / byte[] + encoding (Java 9+)

String immutable hota hai

 aur bhaii log phir hum ye sochte hai string aakhir immutable kyuuu hain 


 Immutability ka matlab:

Ek baar String bana diya → uski value change nahi hoti
Jo bhi “change” lagta hai, actually naya String object banta hai.

String s = "abc";
s = s + "d"; // "abcd"
Yaha:

"abc" alag object

"abcd" ek naya object

s ab naya object point kar raha hai

== → reference comparison (same object?)

equals() → value comparison (same content?)

String s1 = "abc";
String s2 = "abc";
String s3 = new String("abc");

s1 == s2        // true (same pool object)
s1 == s3        // false (different objects)
s1.equals(s3)    //true 

DSA me hmesha equals() use krna hai string k liyeeee.


Strings Vs StringBuilder vs StringBuffer


---String

Immutable

Har concat naya object banata hai

Chhote operations ke liye thik hai

---  StringBuilder

Mutable, fast

Single-threaded use ke liye

Loop me concat ke liye use ➜ must

StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
sb.append("a");
sb.append("b");   // "ab" in same object

 --- StringBuffer

Same as StringBuilder

But thread-safe (synchronized), isliye slow

Ab zyada use nahi hota in normal code

DSA ke liye:
 String + kabhi-kabhi StringBuilder kaafi hai.



 Common useful String methods (jo tum DSA me baar-baar use karoge)

Let’s quickly list:

String s = "Manjeet Mishra";

 Length
int n = s.length();

 Character access
char c = s.charAt(0);  // 'M'

Substring
String sub = s.substring(0, 7); // "Manjeet"


substring(i, j) → [i, j) (j exclude hota hai)

 Compare
s.equals("test");      // true/false
s.equalsIgnoreCase("manjeet mishra");
s.compareTo("other");  // lexicographical

 Search
s.contains("jeet");
s.indexOf("M");      // first index
s.lastIndexOf("M");  // last index

 Case change
s.toLowerCase();
s.toUpperCase();

 Trim spaces
s.trim();            // left + right se spaces hata deta

 Split and join
String[] parts = s.split(" ");
String joined = String.join("-", parts);

 Replace
s.replace('e', 'x');
s.replace("Man", "Code");

 Convert to char array
char[] arr = s.toCharArray();


DSA me useful jab tum in-place modify karna chahte ho.

*/